arts.ttl: ‘Your dad scored on your due date’: Tyler Goodrham celebrates special day in style
arts.sum: TYLER Goodrham was delighted to net a corking equaliser for Oxford United on the same day he is expecting his first child.

arts.ttl: Neil Harris frustrated by Millwall sharing spoils against Oxford United
arts.sum: Up until that point Millwall had done an excellent job nullifying the hosts and had finally made one of a multitude of first-half set-pieces count when Japhet Tanganga headed in Joe Bryan’s deep corner on the stroke of half-time. Oxford played better second half but without creating any chances until the goal.

arts.ttl: Dad-to-be Tyler Goodrham salvages late draw with long-range belter
arts.sum: TYLER Goodrham netted a late screamer to rescue a point for Oxford United on the same day his partner is due to give birth to their first child.

arts.ttl: Oxford earn late point against Millwall
Why Oxford United is not just a football club – and how it contributes to the county
arts.sum: THIS week, we want to call to mind and celebrate some of the work of Oxford United and its community trust for the community across Oxford and Oxfordshire, write Ben Heath and Trevor Lambert of OxVox.

arts.ttl: Man charged and NAMED after “throwing missile” onto Oxford United pitch
arts.sum: An Oxford United fan has been charged with throwing a missile onto the pitch at a Championship game.

arts.ttl: U’s have plan as due date for Tyler Goodrham’s partner is Millwall game
arts.sum: OXFORD United have a plan in place should Tyler Goodrham get the call that his partner is going into labour this weekend.
Jamie Griffith has provided a score prediction for all 12 matches taking place in the Championship this weekend.

arts.ttl: Preview: Oxford United vs. Millwall - prediction, team news, lineups
arts.sum: Sports Mole previews Saturday's Championship clash between Oxford United and Millwall, including predictions, team news and possible lineups.

arts.ttl: Highly unusual situation for Millwall head coach after power failure scuppers Portsmouth fixture
arts.sum: Millwall head coach Neil Harris was placed in the unusual scenario of beginning to prepare for Saturday’s Championship fixture at Oxford United at the time when his side should have been in action against Portsmouth. “We thank Portsmouth for allowing us to do it – a lot of clubs wouldn’t,” Harris told Millwall TV .
